TO MY DEAR NIECE,

JESSY CAROLINE DAVIES,

WHO, BY EXPRESSING A WISH THAT I WOULD WRITE A BOOK FOR "LITTLE PEOPLE,"
LIKE HERSELF, FIRST SUGGESTED TO ME THE COMPOSITION OF THE FOLLOWING
TALES,

THESE PAGES ARE INSCRIBED BY

HER AFFECTIONATE AUNT,

ANNA ELIZA BRAY.

THE VICARAGE, TAVISTOCK,  
*August 5th*, 1853.

